Leaders from Kilifi county have accused the national government of failing to provide adequate security to residents of Chakama and other remote villages. Led by Kilifi Governor Amason Kingi , Magarini MP Michael Kingi and Malindi legislator Aisha Jumwa the leaders accused Interior Cabinet secretary Dr. Fred Matiang’i of laxity in dealing with security in the region. The leaders demanded police stations be set up immediately and vehicles dispatched to Chakama and other hotspots so as to prevent incidents of the nature where a 23 year old Italian aid worker was kidnapped and five other Kenyans injured on Tuesday, arising in future. The two called for the impeachment of the Interior CS terming him a ‘media CS’ who does not even honor summons of members of the National Assembly.  